verbose_text: While the loss of Hs2st affected [Fgf8] amplitude stability (XREF_FIG N) and loss of Hs6st1 caused increased [Fgf8] amplitude (XREF_FIG O), we noticed that both Hs2st -/- and Hs6st1 -/- tissues challenged with an Fgf8 bead eventually approached WT levels of [Fgf8] amplitude (compare XREF_FIG N, O to L 4-h time points).
